{
  "text": "We register our EC2 instances with a target group. This tells the load balancer which instances should receive traffic. We register both web servers we created earlier. The load balancer will now distribute incoming requests across these instances. If one instance becomes unhealthy, traffic automatically routes to the healthy instance. We can add or remove instances from the target group at any time, and the load balancer will automatically adjust. This provides both high availability and the ability to scale.",
